<p id="заболевание-также-известно-как" class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Excessive
vomiting during pregnancy</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>What is excessive pregnancy
vomiting?</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Excessive pregnancy vomiting
is uncontrolled vomiting during pregnancy, leading to fluid and electrolyte
imbalance, ketosis, and weight loss.</span></p>
<p id="причины" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>The disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Uncontrollable vomiting during pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Hyperemesis of pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>In English, the disease is
called Hyperemesis gravidarum.</span></p>

<p id="кто-в-группе-риска" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Excessive vomiting of pregnant
women is a manifestation of severe toxicosis.&nbsp;The leading role in the
development of toxicosis is given to violations of the relationship between the
activity of the central nervous system and internal organs.&nbsp;Violation of
the physiological relationships between the maternal organism and the
trophoblast leads to&nbsp;<i>pathological impulses in the cortex and
subcortical structures of the CNS&nbsp;</i>with the emergence of response
autonomic disorders.&nbsp;Hormonal changes during pregnancy matter, especially
an increase in the level of&nbsp;<i>human chorionic hormone&nbsp;</i>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Risk factors:</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>obesity;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>first pregnancy;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>multiple pregnancy;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>chronic diseases accompanied by impaired tissue trophism and
reduced nutrition;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>pregnancy diabetes;</span></p>

<p id="как-часто-встречается" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>the age of the primipara is over 30 years;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>nausea and vomiting of pregnant women during a previous pregnancy;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>thyroid disease;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>mental disorders;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>dental diseases;</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>bronchial asthma;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>smoking.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p id="симптомы" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Excessive vomiting occurs with
a frequency of 3-10 cases per 1000 pregnancies, more often in urban
women.&nbsp;Unlike nausea and vomiting of pregnant women, excessive vomiting
worries women not only in the morning, but also during the day.&nbsp;Excessive
vomiting of pregnancy develops in about 2% of pregnant women with nausea and
vomiting of pregnancy.&nbsp;Excessive vomiting is usually first diagnosed early
in the first trimester, from weeks 4 to 10.&nbsp;</span><span lang=RU
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Symptoms
may persist until the 18-20th week.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Indomitable vomiting (up to 20 times a day).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Decrease in body weight by 5% or more from the initial weight.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Hypersalivation (increased secretion of saliva).</span></p>

<p id="диагностика-заболевания" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Stomach ache.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Increase in blood pressure.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Headaches, dizziness.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Increase in body temperature.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Increased heart rate.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Jaundice of the sclera of the eyes and skin.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>CNS lesions (delirium, coma, euphoria).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Interrogation and inspection</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>The doctor interviews the
woman about the duration and frequency of vomiting of this
pregnancy.&nbsp;Detailed information is collected on the history and current
data on chronic diseases of the woman.&nbsp;The doctor finds out information
about previous pregnancies, their complications and outcome.&nbsp;The presence
of aggravated heredity, tuberculosis, syphilis, mental, oncological diseases,
bad habits (smoking, alcohol, drugs) is specified.&nbsp;The doctor measures
body temperature, blood pressure and heart rate, conducts an objective
examination of the visible mucous membranes and skin of a woman, checks for the
presence of acetone breath from the mouth.</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Laboratory examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>General clinical blood test&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>with
the determination of hemoglobin, hematocrit, erythrocytes, leukocytes and ESR
to assess anemia and inflammatory syndrome.&nbsp;With excessive vomiting of
pregnant women, an increase in hematocrit (more than 42%) and leukocytosis
(more than 9 x 109 / l) are noted.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>General analysis of urine with sediment microscopy&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>- with
excessive vomiting of pregnant women, proteinuria, cylindruria, urobilinuria,
erythrocyturia, leukocyturia, the appearance of bile pigments are noted.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Bacteriological culture of urine&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>is
performed to diagnose urinary tract infections, which can prolong the duration
of excessive vomiting of pregnant women (even in cases of asymptomatic
bacteuria).&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Urinalysis for the determination of ketone bodies&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>- with
indomitable vomiting of pregnant women, a sharply positive reaction of urine to
acetone is noted.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Biochemical blood test&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>with the determination
of total protein, albumin, globulins, urea, creatinine, direct and indirect
bilirubin, glucose, aspartate aminotransferase (AST), alanine aminotransferase
(ALT), alkaline phosphatase, sodium amylase, potassium, calcium, magnesium,
phosphorus and iron for timely diagnosis of pathological conditions of
women.&nbsp;With excessive vomiting of pregnant women, there is an increase in
the level of residual nitrogen, urea, bilirubin, a slight decrease in total
protein, a decrease in the content of albumins, cholesterol, potassium,
chlorides.&nbsp;Elevated levels of ALT and AST occur in 50% of cases of
excessive vomiting during pregnancy and are rapidly reduced with
treatment.&nbsp;Amylase is elevated in 10% of pregnant women with intractable vomiting
and requires the exclusion of the diagnosis of pancreatitis.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Determination of the content of&nbsp;<b>thyroid-stimulating
hormone (TSH) and free thyroxine (T4)&nbsp;</b>in the blood is carried out with
indomitable vomiting in pregnant women to diagnose thyroid diseases.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Study of&nbsp;<b>hemostasis&nbsp;</b>(blood coagulation
system).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Functional, radiation
and instrumental diagnostics</span></b></p>

<p id="лечение" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Ultrasound examination of the abdominal organs (ultrasound)&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>is
performed to exclude fatty degeneration of the liver in case of excessive
vomiting of pregnant women.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Magnetic resonance and computed tomography&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>are
performed with the duration of excessive vomiting later than the 20th-22nd week
of pregnancy for differential diagnosis with other diseases (gastrointestinal
tract, central nervous system).&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Treatment Goals</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Restoration of water-salt
balance, metabolism and functions of vital organs.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Pregnant women need to follow
a diet, food should be easily digestible and rich in vitamins.&nbsp;You need to
eat often, in small portions.&nbsp;It is necessary to limit the use of foods
that are difficult to digest: smoked meats, fatty meats, spicy and
salty.&nbsp;Drinking should be alkaline: mineral water without gas, herbal
teas, weak tea with lemon, liquids at room temperature or cool.&nbsp;Pregnant
women with excessive vomiting are hospitalized.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Drug treatment of excessive
vomiting in pregnancy begins with the appointment of balanced&nbsp;<i>vitamin-mineral
complexes&nbsp;</i>, then with vomiting lasting &#8805; 3 weeks, they switch to
monotherapy with&nbsp;<i>B vitamins (pyridoxine and thiamine)&nbsp;</i>.&nbsp;<i>Sedative
therapy&nbsp;</i>,&nbsp;<i>antiemetic (antiemic) drugs of&nbsp;</i>various
types of action, including drugs based on pyridoxine (vitamin B6), ginger root
and mint tablets, as well as drugs with propulsive and antihistamine mechanisms
of action,&nbsp;are also used for treatment .&nbsp;Replenishment of fluid loss,
correction of electrolyte imbalance and acid-base balance are carried out
through natural nutrition, through a nasoenteric tube and intravenously.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p id="возможные-осложнения" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Procedures</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Electrosleep.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Electroanalgesia.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Acupressure.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Recovery and improvement of
the quality of life</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>As a rule, after the 20th week
of pregnancy, excessive vomiting stops, after which the pregnant woman can
expand the diet as tolerance increases.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Possible Complications</span></b></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Rupture and perforation of the esophagus.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Pneumothorax (the appearance of air in the pleural cavity).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Pneumomediastinum (the appearance of air in the mediastinum).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>encephalopathy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Blindness.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Liver diseases.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Loss of consciousness, coma.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Renal failure.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Pancreatitis.</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Deep venous thrombosis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Pulmonary embolism.</span></p>

<p id="профилактика" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Central pontine myelinolysis (non-inflammatory demyelination in
the region of the middle part of the base of the pons of the brain).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Rhabdomyolysis (destruction of skeletal muscle tissue).</span></p>

<p  class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Vitamin K deficiency and coagulopathy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Rupture of the spleen.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Sepsis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Fatty infiltration of the placenta.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Prevention</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>A pregnant woman should know
that a physiologically proceeding pregnancy may be accompanied by nausea and
vomiting in the morning no more than 2-3 times a day.&nbsp;To avoid the
development of excessive vomiting in the early stages and in the second
trimester, the following recommendations should be observed:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Reception of vitamin and mineral complexes.&nbsp;Nausea and
vomiting are often caused by vitamin B deficiency.</span></p>

<p id="прогноз" class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Refusal of coffee.&nbsp;This drink irritates the gastric mucosa,
due to its use during pregnancy, it can even make you feel sick from water.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Walks in the fresh air at any time of the day.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>Complete sleep.&nbsp;Sleep deprivation is a fairly common cause of
second trimester nausea.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Book Antiqua"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;
color:black'>No stress.&nbsp;Nervous tension can also cause vomiting.</span></p>

<p id="какие-вопросы-нужно-задать-врачу" class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>Forecast</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Book Antiqua",serif;color:black'>The prognosis for the timely
treatment of excessive vomiting of pregnant women for the mother and fetus is
favorable.&nbsp;With the ineffectiveness of all types of treatment and the
persistence of severe water and electrolyte disorders, termination of pregnancy
is indicated.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
